      "seed": 1000830832,
      "version": 459,
      "versionNonce": 2012330864,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777055724415,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "i/2 if remainder 1 then\ngroup A\nelse group B\n\nML model is basicaly\na mathematical function\n\nThese function can be\ncomplex or easy,most\nof the time 99% they are\npre written, we just have \nto import and use.\n\nBut we have more grasp\non whihc funcction\nis more usable at \nwhat time.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "i/2 if remainder 1 then\ngroup A\nelse group B\n\nML model is basicaly\na mathematical function\n\nThese function can be\ncomplex or easy,most\nof the time 99% they are\npre written, we just have \nto import and use.\n\nBut we have more grasp\non whihc funcction\nis more usable at \nwhat time.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KKApRb0Ayhtu_wyMWElv_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1666.4545404810456,
      "y": 45653.138055997035,
      "width": 506,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#eaddd7",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bZ7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1085607312,
      "version": 779,
      "versionNonce": 666732944,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777056179118,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LIke what kind of i, we have to\ngive to devide by 2, can I give \nABCD or can I give list of values\nlike 1, 2, 3, 4, so making sure \nthat i comes in a particular format\nso these kind of working on data which\nis called as data processing, our most\nof the time will go here only, Once\nour data processing is done, then if we\ngive it to a model and if we ask it to predict\nor classify or something then it will just \ngive it to a function. so lets say I give\nmy i value to the function which is 10\nand it will classify and it goes into B\nand it will return us a result, if we will\nprint the result it will be B. this is ML\nfor us in simple world.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LIke what kind of i, we have to\ngive to devide by 2, can I give \nABCD or can I give list of values\nlike 1, 2, 3, 4, so making sure \nthat i comes in a particular format\nso these kind of working on data which\nis called as data processing, our most\nof the time will go here only, Once\nour data processing is done, then if we\ngive it to a model and if we ask it to predict\nor classify or something then it will just \ngive it to a function. so lets say I give\nmy i value to the function which is 10\nand it will classify and it goes into B\nand it will return us a result, if we will\nprint the result it will be B. this is ML\nfor us in simple world.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "k1IeqpWJXLijLtTj4UDvb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1142.34930151046,
      "y": 46314.14831947739,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#eaddd7",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
