    {
      "id": "5xn_yvPKYkzSOfSBiQBBw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 943.8358227235735,
      "y": 48223.994370401466,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ba0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 460245616,
      "version": 875,
      "versionNonce": 1607443056,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777316188498,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LLM can give text, LLM can generate text, they can only work on text nothing more than that\nwhat they do in terms of text is that we give them a particular text like I want a SQL query\nand I have this this table, can you write a SQL query for me.\nIt will understand different points like our points are related to\nSQL,  table name, query,  insertdata\nit will see all the data point and then it will see all the vectors which are to be generated\nand all the sequence and based on that what it will give us, it will not perform a action but\nbased on this it will move in certain direction which will help it find the right query and it\nwill give us the query. Now we can image how powerful these mathematician function must be to\nfigure out this way to move across.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LLM can give text, LLM can generate text, they can only work on text nothing more than that\nwhat they do in terms of text is that we give them a particular text like I want a SQL query\nand I have this this table, can you write a SQL query for me.\nIt will understand different points like our points are related to\nSQL,  table name, query,  insertdata\nit will see all the data point and then it will see all the vectors which are to be generated\nand all the sequence and based on that what it will give us, it will not perform a action but\nbased on this it will move in certain direction which will help it find the right query and it\nwill give us the query. Now we can image how powerful these mathematician function must be to\nfigure out this way to move across.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "5CcIx3f1emU9iA8DM1maP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 898.4100820279411,
      "y": 48512.07034748581,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ba1",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 494398096,
      "version": 562,
      "versionNonce": 1009478256,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777316565882,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For Prompt engineering we have a generic way, that we start by saying work like this, ex -> work \nlike  a experience software engineer and build code for me. So we are setting direction with the\nhelp of prompt that is where prompt engineering comes into picture, the more our prompts are better,\nbetter the direction of our LLM.\nMathematical function will take this input and it will find out nearest reasonable vector to make our\nnext step on. Now how well it will does, depends on prompt.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For Prompt engineering we have a generic way, that we start by saying work like this, ex -> work \nlike  a experience software engineer and build code for me. So we are setting direction with the\nhelp of prompt that is where prompt engineering comes into picture, the more our prompts are better,\nbetter the direction of our LLM.\nMathematical function will take this input and it will find out nearest reasonable vector to make our\nnext step on. Now how well it will does, depends on prompt.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
