      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777569290243,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we have a model which is trained and tested on some data, because we only have some data\nright now, but we know that it might be insufficient. So in that case what we do is we deploy\nthis model and as and when more data is coming or user feedback is coming or anything that\ncan make this model better, we constantly make a parallel pipeline that keeps on improving the\nmodel or keep on revising our model\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we have a model which is trained and tested on some data, because we only have some data\nright now, but we know that it might be insufficient. So in that case what we do is we deploy\nthis model and as and when more data is coming or user feedback is coming or anything that\ncan make this model better, we constantly make a parallel pipeline that keeps on improving the\nmodel or keep on revising our model\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ksbYOm2osMQbKAJwg_xVm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 871.3872192668963,
      "y": 49636.705234988905,
      "width": 1023,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baB",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 656238131,
      "version": 153,
      "versionNonce": 299577043,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777569573444,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Online models are better than offline model,due to we are improvising it regular basis, then \nwhy we need offline models?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Online models are better than offline model,due to we are improvising it regular basis, then \nwhy we need offline models?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ej5HZmJwFpRNXmQWKEjch",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 911.9145630168963,
      "y": 49688.943516238905,
      "width": 1254,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1470486035,
      "version": 2015,
      "versionNonce": 542385523,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777571629590,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Lets say we are shipping a mobile phone, this mobile phone has some ML feature builtin, Now\nif it has some builtin ML features, It is suppose to work without internet also, which means\nI am not having a constant feedback loop, Forget about internet, I can't even ask to my\nuser again and again that whatever I am suggesting you is it good or bad, It will ruin the\nexperience of having a mobile phone, so that is where we try to cut down on those feedback\nloops or constant inputs, we just make sure that in one go no matter how much data, howmuch\ntraining is required, howmuch heavy training is required but we do heavy training in one shot\nand then we deploy a offline model. we make a model near perfection and then we deploy a offline\nmodel.\nLets say there are our IOT devices which are running on the fly or robotics or anything like that\nthere client doesn't need any update in future then in that case we deploy a offline model for them.\n\nGPT -> Online model\nHuman face detection -> offline model\n\n\n1. Data Collection(bad data, Null values or more values 7 values needed , 8 values are give) -> \n2 EDA(Data processing)(Explorately Data Analysis) -> EDA will give the understanding of which ML algo will be used\n3 Refined data split on two parts train data(90%) and test data(10%)\n4 we will train our model with train data and then we will test this using test data\n    as we know ouput for that.\n5 if the output is matching with test data then we will deploy our model otherwise\n    we will do EDA again.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lets say we are shipping a mobile phone, this mobile phone has some ML feature builtin, Now\nif it has some builtin ML features, It is suppose to work without internet also, which means\nI am not having a constant feedback loop, Forget about internet, I can't even ask to my\nuser again and again that whatever I am suggesting you is it good or bad, It will ruin the\nexperience of having a mobile phone, so that is where we try to cut down on those feedback\nloops or constant inputs, we just make sure that in one go no matter how much data, howmuch\ntraining is required, howmuch heavy training is required but we do heavy training in one shot\nand then we deploy a offline model. we make a model near perfection and then we deploy a offline\nmodel.\nLets say there are our IOT devices which are running on the fly or robotics or anything like that\nthere client doesn't need any update in future then in that case we deploy a offline model for them.\n\nGPT -> Online model\nHuman face detection -> offline model\n\n\n1. Data Collection(bad data, Null values or more values 7 values needed , 8 values are give) -> \n2 EDA(Data processing)(Explorately Data Analysis) -> EDA will give the understanding of which ML algo will be used\n3 Refined data split on two parts train data(90%) and test data(10%)\n4 we will train our model with train data and then we will test this using test data\n    as we know ouput for that.\n5 if the output is matching with test data then we will deploy our model otherwise\n    we will do EDA again.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "nuDJbCYa_AfWwo6eLEp_J",
