      "updated": 1777861422753,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> If we dont have that output column then what our model will predict?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> If we dont have that output column then what our model will predict?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6wtF5QKSIwgU1QR5BWLk8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1033.498658128105,
      "y": 51197.08528332592,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bae",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1974387347,
      "version": 1278,
      "versionNonce": 126489779,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777861836251,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It can't predict output.\nThe purpose of unsupervised model is totally different, -> here we have just input, we dont\nhave output. Predicting is one thing, but based on input or data, can we run some maths formula\nto find some pattern in the data. Here in unsupervised learning we run something mathematical\nto find a pattern.\nLets say we have data of urbanisation in Bangalore, Now if we just run some pattern analysis\non it, We can see which areas are over the time being slowly more populated versus where the\npopulation is leaving from, Now based on this we can have some view point on migration, \npeople's migration, From which area to which area they are migrating. For this it is not required\nto have migration data. It is not required from everyone they are migrated or not, I am not\nrequired to ask this question that you guys are migrated or not, We just need data on where they\nare versus, on the last year or last to last year where they were, we just need to have their\ngeographical keypoints. then ML model will itself figure out the pattern. we dont have to do anything.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It can't predict output.\nThe purpose of unsupervised model is totally different, -> here we have just input, we dont\nhave output. Predicting is one thing, but based on input or data, can we run some maths formula\nto find some pattern in the data. Here in unsupervised learning we run something mathematical\nto find a pattern.\nLets say we have data of urbanisation in Bangalore, Now if we just run some pattern analysis\non it, We can see which areas are over the time being slowly more populated versus where the\npopulation is leaving from, Now based on this we can have some view point on migration, \npeople's migration, From which area to which area they are migrating. For this it is not required\nto have migration data. It is not required from everyone they are migrated or not, I am not\nrequired to ask this question that you guys are migrated or not, We just need data on where they\nare versus, on the last year or last to last year where they were, we just need to have their\ngeographical keypoints. then ML model will itself figure out the pattern. we dont have to do anything.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
