    },
    {
      "id": "mM3pxSYqDAwQ5cK4wfWdt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 840.385376878105,
      "y": 53112.94465832592,
      "width": 1210,
      "height": 750,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bax",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1434063859,
      "version": 3295,
      "versionNonce": 1101567773,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777864781423,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Here we can't predict line or whether it is a cat or dog because we dont have data points (output) over\nhere. We can't predict whether it is dog or cat because we dont know, which one is a cat and which one\nis dog. We don't have the labels of the image because label or output is name whether it is a cat or\ndog. We dont have that label here. So what we can do with unsupervised learning\nWith unsupervised learning, lets say we have a table, we can identify which columns are being used to,\nlike one column value is increasing, another is increasing, or someone is increasing then other is \ndecreasing, so which one proportional , which one is inversally proportional or which one is not at all\nuseful like this column has no impact whether anything is increasing or decreasing. which means it will\nnot impact anything, that I want to figure out over here. This is more or less a useless column for us.\nSo in this case what we try and do is find out relationship between various columns that we have in the\ndata. \nNow when we have various columns and we have to find out relationship, obviously there are going to be \ncertain columns, which are not at all related to each other. So it this case we will completely remove\nthose columns. This is called as dimentionality reduction.\nSo here we are compressing data, only keep meaning ful data.\nIn unsupervised learning it is finding pattern by themself, It might possible it is finding wrong pattern\n-> No it is math\n\nIt might possible it is finding wrong pattern, but ye kab hota hai job, for even in dimentionality reduction\nthere are n number of algorithms, I'm suppose to use A algorithm but I am using B then we will get no results.\nand whihc algorithm to use, we will get idea from EDA. EDA is the most important thing that we can do in our\nwhole Machine Learning. If we are good at EDA, we are good at everything, if we are not goot at EDA, we are\nnot at all good at Machine Learning. Because when we do EDA, once we understand the data, once we understand\nthe pattern, we will understand the requirement of what algorithms will be used. Once we are good at EDA, the\nonly thing that we need to do in life is give 10-15 minutes for each model not more than that, import \nlogistic regresssion use logistic regression, import liner regression use linear regression, import XGboost,\nimport scikit learn, use XGboost, use scikit learn that is it. Because after that we will know that these\nkind of models are there, And once we know the models,once we know the EDA. We can know which model is to use\nwhere, Knowing model is important, so that we can know, when to apply which one, and EDA is important because\nonly EDA can tell which model will be more releavant now.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Here we can't predict line or whether it is a cat or dog because we dont have data points (output) over\nhere. We can't predict whether it is dog or cat because we dont know, which one is a cat and which one\nis dog. We don't have the labels of the image because label or output is name whether it is a cat or\ndog. We dont have that label here. So what we can do with unsupervised learning\nWith unsupervised learning, lets say we have a table, we can identify which columns are being used to,\nlike one column value is increasing, another is increasing, or someone is increasing then other is \ndecreasing, so which one proportional , which one is inversally proportional or which one is not at all\nuseful like this column has no impact whether anything is increasing or decreasing. which means it will\nnot impact anything, that I want to figure out over here. This is more or less a useless column for us.\nSo in this case what we try and do is find out relationship between various columns that we have in the\ndata. \nNow when we have various columns and we have to find out relationship, obviously there are going to be \ncertain columns, which are not at all related to each other. So it this case we will completely remove\nthose columns. This is called as dimentionality reduction.\nSo here we are compressing data, only keep meaning ful data.\nIn unsupervised learning it is finding pattern by themself, It might possible it is finding wrong pattern\n-> No it is math\n\nIt might possible it is finding wrong pattern, but ye kab hota hai job, for even in dimentionality reduction\nthere are n number of algorithms, I'm suppose to use A algorithm but I am using B then we will get no results.\nand whihc algorithm to use, we will get idea from EDA. EDA is the most important thing that we can do in our\nwhole Machine Learning. If we are good at EDA, we are good at everything, if we are not goot at EDA, we are\nnot at all good at Machine Learning. Because when we do EDA, once we understand the data, once we understand\nthe pattern, we will understand the requirement of what algorithms will be used. Once we are good at EDA, the\nonly thing that we need to do in life is give 10-15 minutes for each model not more than that, import \nlogistic regresssion use logistic regression, import liner regression use linear regression, import XGboost,\nimport scikit learn, use XGboost, use scikit learn that is it. Because after that we will know that these\nkind of models are there, And once we know the models,once we know the EDA. We can know which model is to use\nwhere, Knowing model is important, so that we can know, when to apply which one, and EDA is important because\nonly EDA can tell which model will be more releavant now.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
