    {
      "id": "66iFlqZbDJ8xj9J3_2BcW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 877.576783128105,
      "y": 53931.11653332592,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bb0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1033041917,
      "version": 1516,
      "versionNonce": 884704723,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777865659168,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Even when we learn, we will only learn how EDA is done, Noone can make us good at EDA. We will only\nbe good at EDA, more will do it and the more by interest we are doing it. Like we have 4 dataset but\nwe are not satisfied, we are going to kaggle, and downloading 40 different datasets. Trying to run\ndifferent kind of EDA. trying to see what are the column that are there, Once we see 20, 30, 40\ndatasets, we will be like, yaar isse jada kuchh ho hi ni skta, like ek limit aa jati h\n\nFor example,\n like there is a gender, which we have to convert into 0, 1, there is True, False that we have to convert\nto 0, 1 so at the end of the day, they are just, 0,1 for us. There is salary that will come in certain\nrange. There are going to be Null values, we have to deal with null values. Or row and columns, we have\nto deal with them. So at the end of the day, when we convert everything to numbers there are very few\npatterns that we can find in EDA, And then what we have to see is which one is relate to what, for that we\nplot some graph, when we plot a graph, when we are trying to draw a line or something.\n\nClear representation of this ->\n    lets say we are using two ML models, to present a graph for male and female\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Even when we learn, we will only learn how EDA is done, Noone can make us good at EDA. We will only\nbe good at EDA, more will do it and the more by interest we are doing it. Like we have 4 dataset but\nwe are not satisfied, we are going to kaggle, and downloading 40 different datasets. Trying to run\ndifferent kind of EDA. trying to see what are the column that are there, Once we see 20, 30, 40\ndatasets, we will be like, yaar isse jada kuchh ho hi ni skta, like ek limit aa jati h\n\nFor example,\n like there is a gender, which we have to convert into 0, 1, there is True, False that we have to convert\nto 0, 1 so at the end of the day, they are just, 0,1 for us. There is salary that will come in certain\nrange. There are going to be Null values, we have to deal with null values. Or row and columns, we have\nto deal with them. So at the end of the day, when we convert everything to numbers there are very few\npatterns that we can find in EDA, And then what we have to see is which one is relate to what, for that we\nplot some graph, when we plot a graph, when we are trying to draw a line or something.\n\nClear representation of this ->\n    lets say we are using two ML models, to present a graph for male and female\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
